  "footnotes": [
    "Gulf column (slots:4) covers the eastern Arabian littoral; in earlier periods they share the same political history, splitting into UAE, Qatar, Bahrain, and Kuwait only at independence (1961–1971)",
    "Nejd (central plateau) was rarely under direct external control; the Wahhabi-Saudi alliance originating here unified most of the peninsula by 1932",
    "Hejaz (Red Sea coast) contains Mecca and Medina; it was the religious heartland of Islam and the prize sought by every Islamic polity",
    "The Zaydi Imamate in Yemen persisted through the Ottoman period as a recurring revolt state; it became the Mutawakkilite Kingdom after WWI",
    "Oman's Ibadi Imamate tradition is one of the oldest continuous political-religious institutions in the Islamic world",
    "In the Contemporary row, Nejd and Hejaz are unified under Saudi Arabia (spanning both columns)"
